# Apex domains for the framework's own marketing site — Netlify is serving

# its default \*.netlify.app wildcard cert instead of a Let's Encrypt cert

# matching the apex domain, so lychee's TLS verification fails. Pinned

# here so framework PRs aren't blocked on adopter-side DNS / cert config.

# Fix is in Netlify dashboard (Site → Domain management → HTTPS →

# Provision certificate), separate concern from any framework diff.

https://me2resh\.com._
https://yard\.apexscript\.com._

# v3 removed the site/ marketing dir; stale relative links to it (e.g. in

# docs/agdr/AgDR-0018) are dead by design on this fork.

site/index\.html
